sentences: Vittorio Camardese (Potenza, 6 July 1929 – 2 July 2010) was an Italian guitarist and physician, most famous among musicians and general audiences for his 'tapping' style of guitar playing.
The same year also saw Camardese's final television appearance.
The only widely-available film of his playing is his performance Chitarra, amore mio, rebroadcast in later years by the Italian state broadcaster RAI.
A project to document Camardese's life and work is (as of May 2016) seeking funding.
